{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:57:44.027843+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the README and CI scripts, here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n**Important context:** This project's `web/` directory is an **AngularDart** progressive web app (not a Flutter web app). The README describes two separate projects:\n\n| Directory | Framework | Build output |\n|-----------|-----------|-------------|\n| `web/` | AngularDart | `web/build/` |\n| `mobile/` | Flutter | `mobile/build/web/` (if built for web) |\n\nThe pattern `build/web/` is specifically the output location for **Flutter's** web target (`flutter build web`).\n\n---\n\n### If you want to build the **Flutter mobile app** for the web target (outputs to `build/web/`):\n\n```bash\n# (a) Install Flutter web tooling\nflutter config --enable-web\n\n# (b) Fetch dependencies for the project\ncd core && pub get && cd ..\ncd mobile && flutter packages get && cd ..\n\n# (c) Produce a release web build under build/web/\ncd mobile && flutter build web\n# → output lands at mobile/build/web/\n```\n\n> **Note:** Per the README's \"Development environment setup\" section, this project was built with **Flutter 1.0**, which predates Flutter web support. You'll need a modern Flutter SDK (≥2.x) for `flutter build web` to work, and the codebase may require migration.\n\n---\n\n### If you want to build the **AngularDart web project** (the project's own web app):\n\n```bash\n# (a) Install Dart SDK for web + webdev tooling\n# (Install standalone Dart SDK from https://dart.dev/get-dart)\npub global activate webdev\n\n# (b) Fetch dependencies\ncd core && pub get && cd ..\ncd web && pub get && cd ..\n\n# (c) Produce a release web build\ncd web && webdev build --release --output build\n# → output lands at web/build/ (not build/web/)\n```\n\nThe README itself only mentions `webdev serve` (dev server) and doesn't document a release build command, but `webdev build` is the standard webdev command for production 